article.headline: Cent. Arkansas 68, Hendrix College 40
article.story: CONWAY, Ark. -- Jared Reheml scored 16 points, and Central Arkansas beat crosstown foe Hendrix College 68-40 on Friday night. Reheml was 4 of 7 from beyond the 3-point arc, and junior center Chris Williams added 10 points off the bench for Central Arkansas. The Bears were able to force the Division III school into 22 turnovers, shooting 39.7 percent from the field while holding Hendrix to just 28.6 percent. Central Arkansas plays Tennessee Tech on Monday night.
